According to Paris police,&nbsp;Kim Kardashian was&nbsp;robbed at gunpoint at a luxury Paris residence&nbsp;at around 3 a.m. local time (0100UTC) on Monday. The 35-year-old was tied up and locked in the bathroom.The five attackers were reportedly wearing ski masks and jackets with police signs. A&nbsp;jewelry box, containing five to six million euros worth of jewels, and a ring worth around four million euros were stolen in the incident.Kardashian's&nbsp;spokesperson Ina Treciokas said the&nbsp;reality TV star and selfie aficionada was "badly shaken but physically unharmed."It wasn't immediately clear whether her two children, 3-year-old daughter North and 10-month-old son Saint, were also in the hotel room. Send Facebook Twitter Google+ Whatsapp Tumblr linkedin stumble Digg reddit Newsvine Permalink http://dw.com/p/2QpZV'Family emergency'Kardashian's husband, rapper Kanye West, was headlining at the New York festival The&nbsp;Meadows at the time of the robbery.&nbsp;West abruptly ended the performance an&nbsp;hour into his set.A representative told festival-goers that the rapper had left due to a "family emergency."Kardashian is currently in the French capital for Paris Fashion Week, along with her mother, Kris Jenner, and sisters, Kourtney Kardashian and Kendall Jenner.ksb/kl&nbsp;(AP, AFP, Reuters, dpa)&nbsp;